# 📘 Course Title:  
**Basic Computing and MS Office – Beginner to Pro**

---

## 👨‍🏫 Course Incharge:  
**Abdul Basit**

---

## 👥 Who Can Join?
- No prior IT experience needed  
- Basic computer literacy is enough  
- Perfect for beginners looking to start their digital journey

---

## 📚 Course Overview  
This beginner-friendly course helps you build hands-on skills using essential IT tools used in modern workplaces. You’ll:
- Create professional documents, spreadsheets, and presentations  
- Learn foundational programming logic  
- Understand how networking works (IP, DNS, domains)  
- Use Git and GitHub for version control  
- Leverage AI tools like ChatGPT to boost productivity  
- Build a personal portfolio to showcase your digital skills

---

## 🎯 What You’ll Learn
- ✅ Use Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint & Google Workspace  
- ✅ Understand and apply basic programming logic  
- ✅ Get familiar with IP addresses, domain names, and DNS  
- ✅ Use Git & GitHub for version control and collaboration  
- ✅ Apply AI tools for writing, data analysis, and content creation  
- ✅ Build a complete digital portfolio to launch your career

---

## 🗓️ 10-Week Course Plan

### 📅 **Week 1: IT Fundamentals & Career Overview**
- Overview of IT roles (developer, analyst, designer, etc.)  
- Freelancing vs full-time jobs vs starting your own business  
- Tools/platforms used in the course  
- 🔧 **Hands-on:** Explore job portals and online IT communities  

---

### 📅 **Week 2: Documents – Basics to Advanced**
- MS Word & Google Docs basics  
- Formatting, styles, templates, TOC, citations  
- Collaboration and export options  
- 🔧 **Hands-on:** Create a resume + format a professional report  

---

### 📅 **Week 3: Spreadsheets – Foundations**
- Excel & Google Sheets basics (cells, formulas, formatting)  
- Functions: `SUM`, `AVERAGE`, `MIN`, `MAX`  
- Sorting, filtering, basic charts  
- 🔧 **Hands-on:** Create a personal budget + mini dashboard  

---

### 📅 **Week 4: Spreadsheets – Advanced**
- Pivot tables  
- `VLOOKUP` and `IF` statements  
- Dropdowns, validations, real-world data tasks  
- 🔧 **Hands-on:** Analyze product or employee dataset  

---

### 📅 **Week 5: Presentations & Visual Design**
- PowerPoint & Google Slides layout/design  
- Inserting visuals, transitions, and animations  
- Tips for strong, professional slides  
- 🔧 **Hands-on:** Create a 5-slide IT career presentation  

---

### 📅 **Week 6: Logic Building for Programming**
- Why logic matters in programming  
- Variables, loops, conditions, and algorithms  
- Scratch or flowcharts for visual logic practice  
- 🔧 **Hands-on:** Solve simple logic tasks (calculator, age checker, etc.)  

---

### 📅 **Week 7: Applied Programming & Online Coding**
- Intro to platforms like Replit or Google Colab  
- Writing/test-driving basic Python code  
- Logical thinking through code challenges  
- 🔧 **Hands-on:** Solve 3–5 mini challenges in Python or pseudocode  

---

### 📅 **Week 8: Networking Basics**
- IP addresses and how DNS works  
- What is a domain and how to register one  
- Tools: `whois`, `nslookup`, DNS records  
- 🔧 **Hands-on:** Inspect real domains and perform DNS lookups  

---

### 📅 **Week 9: Git, GitHub & AI Tools**
- Version control with Git (repos, commits, branches)  
- Creating and pushing projects to GitHub  
- Introduction to AI tools: ChatGPT, Gemini, MS Copilot  
- 🔧 **Hands-on:** Push your project to GitHub + generate content/code using AI  

---

### 📅 **Week 10: Final Portfolio Project & Career Planning**
- Combine all your work into one digital portfolio:  
  - ✅ A professional resume (Word/Docs)  
  - ✅ A spreadsheet report (Excel/Sheets)  
  - ✅ A clean presentation (Slides/PowerPoint)  
  - ✅ A GitHub repository with all project files  
- Reflect on what you’ve learned  
- Plan your next step: freelancing, certifications, advanced learning  
- 🔧 **Hands-on:** Submit and present your digital portfolio  

---

## 🧮 Grading Breakdown

| Component                    | Weight (%) |
|-----------------------------|------------|
| Quizzes                     | 20%        |
| Participation & Attendance  | 15%        |
| Weekly Projects             | 25%        |
| Final Portfolio             | 40%        |
| **Total**                   | **100%**   |

